<TITLE> Garment worker run over, killed by bus in Savar </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Savar, Oct 10 (bdnews24.com)  A garment worker died after being run over by a bus at Baipile stand in Savar Saturday morning. Two other workers were injured. Police identified the dead worker as Sathi Aktar, 26, from Akkelpur upazila in Joypurhat, who was working as an operator in a garment factory of N & N Industries at Baipile. The injured were Asma Aktar and Amena Begum, a cleaner and worker of the same factory. Sub-inspector Billal Hossain of Ashulia Police Station said the three started for their workplace at around 7:45am in a rickshaw-van. A bus, carrying workers of Paxar Garments to the DEPZ, hit it from behind in front of Aziz filling station at the Baipile stand on the Dhaka-Tangail highway and killed Sathi on the spot, Hossain told bdnews24.com. The injured were rushed to the Savar Gonoshasthya Nagar Kendro. Amena was released after first aid but Asma was sent to Dhaka Orthopaedic Hospital in a critical state, he said. Police detained the bus and its driver Titu Mia with the help of locals. A case has been filed at the Ashulia Police Station. bdnews2
